The paper deals with interactive communication over noisy channels with feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the design and analysis of protocols, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also considers the resilience of protocols to noise and erasures, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). The use of bounds and algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on resilience and efficiency in communication protocols suggests that it may also be relevant to the field of systems and networking (cs.SI).
